fields.description:
When a user tries to delete a security group that has a running instance using it, Eucalyptus responds back with a bogus error, when the proper response should be an AWS error code and message:

{code}
# euca-delete-group zenlb-test
DeleteSecurityGroupType: Failed to delete security group: zenlb-test for arn:aws:euare::345590850920:user/admin because of: org.hibernate.exception.ConstraintViolationException: could not delete: [com.eucalyptus.network.ExtantNetwork#4028a7e53d268add013d746f32b31dbc]
Caused by: org.postgresql.util.PSQLException: ERROR: update or delete on table "metadata_extant_network" violates foreign key constraint "fkbdc151865dab4005" on table "metadata_network_indices"
  Detail: Key (id)=(4028a7e53d268add013d746f32b31dbc) is still referenced from table "metadata_network_indices".
{code}

When testing against AWS, here is the error code and message:

{code}
$ ec2-delete-group neo4j-cluster
Client.InvalidGroup.InUse: There are active instances using security group 'neo4j-cluster'
{code}

To confirm that this wasn't a euca2ools issue, test ran with euca2ools confirms that the issue is with the response from the CLC:

{code}
# euca-delete-group -a XXXXXX -s XXXXXX --url http://us-east-1.ec2.amazonaws.com neo4j-cluster
InvalidGroup.InUse: There are active instances using security group 'neo4j-cluster'
{code}

*Reference*

* http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/APIReference/api-error-codes.html
